//! REAL external accept-KAT fixture — **Base mainnet output 12086, proven out of
//! Ethereum L1 mainnet state**. Every proof and value below was captured from
//! public nodes (publicnode.com for L1, blastapi.io archive for Base L2); nothing
//! is a round-trip construction:
//!
//! * The OP output proposal: Base `L2OutputOracle` (proxy
//!   0x56315b90c40730925ec5485cf004d835058518A0 on L1) `getL2Output(12086)` =
//!   (outputRoot 0x3b4c…3a0a, timestamp 1730303687, l2BlockNumber 21756600) — the
//!   LAST legacy-oracle output before Base's fault-proof migration.
//! * The L1 anchor: `eth_getProof` on L1 mainnet at FINALIZED block 25514490 for
//!   the oracle account + the two `l2Outputs[12086]` element slots
//!   (`keccak256(uint256(3)) + 2*12086` and +1).
//! * The output-root preimage: Base block 21756600's REAL header
//!   (stateRoot/hash via mainnet.base.org) + the REAL `L2ToL1MessagePasser`
//!   (0x4200…0016) storageHash at that block (blastapi archive `eth_getProof`);
//!   keccak256(0^32 ‖ stateRoot ‖ messagePasserStorageRoot ‖ blockHash) equals the
//!   on-chain output root EXACTLY — external conformance of the v0 field order.
//! * The L2 holding: `eth_getProof` on Base at block 21756600 for WETH
//!   (0x4200…0006, `balanceOf` mapping slot 3) held by the Uniswap V3 WETH/USDC
//!   pool 0xd0b5…F224 — 2388840386918579889861 wei (~2388.84 WETH).
//!
//! The ONLY constructed element in the accept test is the `FinalizedExecution`
//! carrier (`new_unchecked` with the real L1 block's stateRoot/number/hash) — the
//! sync-committee finality path itself has its own KATs (tests/finality_kat.rs).

